al party, and the factors explaining success or failure. Bridging the academic-policy divide, they identify concrete lessons from previous transformations processes, as well as options for future international involvement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCivil war. 0aLegitimacy of governments. 0aPolitical stability. 0aPolitical violence. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Peace.2bisacsh1 aGiustozzi, Antonio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoor, Luc van de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aManning, Carrie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNindorera, Willy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichards, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScholey, Pamela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVincent, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoung, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZeeuw, Jeroen de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 ade Zeeuw, Jeroen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078425140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978162637349540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781626373495423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781626373495/original  a978-3-11-078425-1  Lynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles